even with pigeons 'cause they ruined a $400 suit.

01:40:25.352 --> 01:40:27.912
Now, uh, there's no percentage in that...

01:40:28.022 --> 01:40:31.458
because there are probably
10 million pigeons in Boston alone...

01:40:31.558 --> 01:40:33.992
all of them laying eggs every day...

01:40:34.094 --> 01:40:36.562
which generally produce more pigeons...

01:40:36.663 --> 01:40:41.566
all, uh, dropping tons and tons of shit
every day, rain or shine.

01:40:41.668 --> 01:40:45.195
And this guy in New York,
he's gonna, well -

01:40:45.305 --> 01:40:48.672
There just aren't gonna be
any more of them in this world.

01:40:50.744 --> 01:40:53.645
Yeah, a man gets desperate.

01:40:53.747 --> 01:40:56.648
He does a few things,
he knows it won't work.

01:40:56.750 --> 01:41:00.083
Pretty soon he quits, packs it all in,
goes away someplace.

01:41:00.187 --> 01:41:02.087
It's the only way there is.

01:41:02.189 --> 01:41:05.488
Okay, you gave us Scalise,
and we're grateful.

01:41:05.592 --> 01:41:08.959
You can't talk about Coyle,
you can't talk about Coyle. It's all right.

01:41:09.063 --> 01:41:11.031
- Thanks.
- Screw.

01:41:11.131 --> 01:41:14.532
We've been friends a long time now.

01:41:14.635 --> 01:41:19.402
I never asked a friend yet to do somethin'
he really couldn't do, I knew he couldn't do it.

